of the government.

00:44:03.090 --> 00:44:06.430
YOANI SANCHEZ:
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

00:44:06.430 --> 00:44:10.430
TRANSLATOR: And for them, I
am a kind of internet devil.

00:44:10.430 --> 00:44:21.727
YOANI SANCHEZ:
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

00:44:21.727 --> 00:44:23.310
TRANSLATOR: And so
I imagine that it's

00:44:23.310 --> 00:44:27.000
very difficult for an
instructor of anything

00:44:27.000 --> 00:44:29.990
that touches the internet, and
who has a more modern mind,

00:44:29.990 --> 00:44:34.602
to be teaching anything that
touches with technology.

00:44:34.602 --> 00:44:36.240
MARY GROVE: Last
question, if I may.

00:44:36.240 --> 00:44:40.135
What is your greatest hope
for Cuba and for the future?

00:44:40.135 --> 00:44:44.380
YOANI SANCHEZ:
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

00:44:44.380 --> 00:44:46.790
TRANSLATOR: I think
that Cuba needs freedom.

00:44:46.790 --> 00:44:52.840
YOANI SANCHEZ:
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

00:44:52.840 --> 00:44:55.710
TRANSLATOR: The freedom to
stand on a corner and scream,

00:44:55.710 --> 00:44:56.830
there's no liberty here.

00:44:56.830 --> 00:45:03.529
YOANI SANCHEZ:
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

00:45:03.529 --> 00:45:06.070
TRANSLATOR: The day that I can
do that in a street in Havana,

00:45:06.070 --> 00:45:08.607
I will feel that my country
has entered the future.

00:45:08.607 --> 00:45:10.940
MARY GROVE: On behalf of all
of us here, muchas gracias.

00:45:10.940 --> 00:45:11.540
YOANI SANCHEZ: Muchas gracias.

00:45:11.540 --> 00:45:12.440
Thank you very much.

00:45:12.440 --> 00:45:15.599
[APPLAUSE]

00:45:15.599 --> 00:45:16.640
YOANI SANCHEZ: Thank you.

